- In lower left panel (\'93Three possible models\'94) the output of the delayed normalization filter is depicted as producing a neural response that extends longer in time than shown for the earlier stages (the linear and CTS). This does not seem to be the case for the depiction of the model output shown in the next panel over (\'93ECoG design and predictions\'94). My interpretation is that the x-axis has been expanded in the first instance to show the form of the output. Is this correct?\
